Dropping Columns¶

Dropping above columns above because some have one one value, some have an overwhelming majority of one value, with others numbering less than 70 - when total is 66587, that's ~0.1%. I haven't included the value_counts() of the columns in this notebook to increase readability.
'diag_1', 'diag_2','diag_3','diag_4','X6','X8','X11','X15','X16','X17','X18','X19','X22','X23','X24','X25' - drop these. They are mostly float but a bunch of entries start with letters and there are no explanations.

Encoders For Categorical Columns¶

'race' - Turn this into caucasian vs. non-caucasian. Sounds racist, but there is a disparity in the quality of health-care received by white people and minorities. Also replace the unknown '?' in this column with the majority class, which is (no surprises) caucasian.
'age' - Turn this into a linear scale.
'change', 'diabetesMed' - Simple binary encoder.
'X1','X2','X3','X4','X5','X7','X9','X10','X12','X13','X14','X20','X21' - custom encoders for them. See below.

In [8]:
df['race']=df['race'].replace('?','Caucasian') #replacing with majority class
df = df.drop(df['gender'].loc[df['gender'] == 'Unknown/Invalid'].index,axis=0)

#we'll call the encoder function after plotting
def cat_encoders(df):
    #gender encoding - binary
    enc_gender = {'Female':1,'Male':0}
    df['gender'] = df['gender'].replace(enc_gender)
    
    #age encoded to a linear scale
    enc_age = {'[0-10)':0,'[10-20)':1,'[20-30)':2,'[30-40)':3,'[40-50)':4,
           '[50-60)':5,'[60-70)':6,'[70-80)':7,'[80-90)':8,'[90-100)':9}
    df['age'] = df['age'].replace(enc_age)

    #X encoders
    enc_X1 = {'None':0,'Norm':1,'>200':2,'>300':3}
    df['X1'] = df['X1'].replace(enc_X1)

    enc_X2 = {'None':0,'Norm':2,'>7':2,'>8':3}
    df['X2'] = df['X2'].replace(enc_X2)

    enc_Xn = {'No':0,'Steady':1,'Down':2,'Up':3} #to encode X3, X4, X5, X7, X9, X10, X12, X13, X14, X20, X21
    Xn_cols = ['X3','X4','X5','X7','X9','X10','X12','X13','X14','X20','X21']
    df[Xn_cols] = df[Xn_cols].replace(enc_Xn)

    #encoding change
    enc_ch = {'Ch':1,'No':0}
    df['change'] = df['change'].replace(enc_ch)

    #encoding diabetesMed
    enc_diab = {'Yes':1,'No':0}
    df['diabetesMed'] = df['diabetesMed'].replace(enc_diab)
    
    idx_cau = df['race'].loc[df['race']=='Caucasian'].index
    idx_ncau = df['race'].loc[df['race']!='Caucasian'].index

    df['race'].loc[idx_cau] = 1
    df['race'].loc[idx_ncau] = 0
    
    return df

scaler = MinMaxScaler()
scaler.fit(trainX)

def data_transform(X,y):
    return scaler.transform(X),y

X_train, y_train = data_transform(trainX, trainY)
X_test, y_test = data_transform(testX, testY)

In [20]:
classifiers = [SGDClassifier(),
               GaussianNB(), DecisionTreeClassifier(),
               LGBMClassifier(), CatBoostClassifier(verbose=False),XGBClassifier()]

scores = pd.DataFrame(columns=['Classifier','TestScore','TrainScore'])

for i in classifiers:
    i.fit(X_train, y_train)
    y_pred_test = i.predict(X_test)
    y_pred_train = i.predict(X_train)
    test_score = accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred_test)
    train_score = accuracy_score(y_train, y_pred_train)
    scores.loc[len(scores.index)] = [i.__class__.__name__,test_score,train_score]
